e: ￹`Tanektek~ `ko~ `ka~`tomirengan~ `no~ `loma'~ `niyam~.￺Our home's foundation is stable / strong.￻我們家建的非常堅固
￹`O~ `tanektek~`ay~ `a~ `kilang~ `konini~.￺This piece of wood is strong.￻這是堅實的木材
￹`Tanektek~ `ko~ `tireng~ `nira~.￺His health is good.￻他的身體很強壯
￹`Tanektek~ `to~ `ko~ `katayalan~ `niyam~.￺Our business is secure.￻我上班的公司很穩固
d.f: ￹￺to be strong * stable * established * not easily moved * with extended meanings of good health￻穩固，不容易動搖，延伸其意義為好的健康狀況
